A number of firefighters were injured and taken to hospital. Several vehicles and homes have been destroyed. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Firefighters are monitoring certain spots after containing a fire on Tafelberg Road in Cape Town. Several vehicles and homes were destroyed after the fire broke out on the slopes of Table Mountain on Sunday afternoon. Jermaine Carelse from the City of Cape Town said several firefighters are still battling the blaze. READ: Mountain fire approaching Lion's Head "Currently we have 30 firefighting appliances and over 230 firefighters still on scene. "Luckily for us today, the wind has died down quite a lot. As you know there were several houses that had been lost in this fire and a number of vehicles that were sparked on Signal Hillside area," said Carelse. He said a number of firefighters were injured and have been taken to hospital.